# Product Manager-Oriented Role Output

## Project Overview

The interviews indicate that TechMPower is fundamentally an implementation-coordination problem rather than only a clinical intervention problem.

The project focuses on integrating HIV care and substance use disorder (SUD) treatment within jail-linked environments. Success depends on whether multiple operational stakeholders — correctional health teams, community providers, social workers, implementation teams, and post-release support organizations — can coordinate workflows consistently and sustainably. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

A useful product analogy is that this initiative resembles integrating several existing systems that were never originally designed to work together. The effectiveness of the overall experience depends heavily on the quality of handoffs between stakeholders and service stages.

