# User Problem and Product Goal

The core user problem is fragmented continuity of care.

People living with HIV and individuals with substance use disorder often experience disconnected care workflows across:

- jail intake systems
- correctional healthcare services
- mental health support
- substance use treatment
- community-based providers
- post-release follow-up services

The product-level objective is therefore not only improving access to care, but reducing operational friction across the full service journey. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

From a product management perspective, the “users” include both patients and frontline implementation teams responsible for coordinating care delivery.

