# Stakeholder and Dependency Mapping

The interviews imply a highly interdependent implementation ecosystem involving:

| Stakeholder | Primary Role |
|---|---|
| Correctional health staff | deliver or coordinate care inside jail |
| Social workers / coordinators | patient navigation and service linkage |
| Community organizations | continuity of care after release |
| Implementation champions | encourage evidence-based practice adoption |
| Technical assistance teams | operational support and troubleshooting |

This creates a workflow environment with many dependency handoffs and coordination requirements.

