# Product and Delivery Risks

Several recurring delivery risks appear throughout the interviews:

## Coordination Risk

Care delivery depends on reliable collaboration across independent organizations.

## Adoption Risk

New workflows and technologies may not be consistently adopted by staff.

## Sustainability Risk

Funding limitations and reimbursement constraints may weaken long-term implementation viability.

## Continuity Risk

Transportation and follow-up barriers may disrupt post-release care continuity.

## Technology Fit Risk

Telehealth and related technologies may improve access, but only if they align with local workflows and operational readiness. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}

